The paper discusses domain adaptation for question answering using deep neural networks, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses transfer learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper involves information retrieval and text classification, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses experiments on question answering in the automobile manual domain, which could involve computer vision techniques, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
